<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="426" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-03-22"><hi rend="italic">March 22,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1312.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 1865, of the 26th ultimo, has
                            been received, and your course in refusing to issue to Joseph Duff a
                            passport, under the circumstances set out in the dispatch, is
                            approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>